            <fr:title text="propositional truncation">propositional truncation</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Axiom</fr:taxon>
            <fr:meta name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0028.agda" type="external">erct-0028.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>For any type <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> we have a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001I.xml" title="proposition" addr="forest://erct/erct-001I" type="local">proposition</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {toProp}\,{A}]]></fr:tex> equipped with a unit map <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\eta _{\mathsf {prop}}\colon  A \to \mathsf {toProp}\,{A}]]></fr:tex>; moreover, we have the following induction principle: for any family of <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001H.xml" title="contractible type" addr="forest://erct/erct-001H" type="local">propositions</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B\colon  \mathsf {toProp}\,A \to  \mathsf {Prop}]]></fr:tex>, any function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b\colon  \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}} B
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen \eta _{\mathsf {prop}}\,x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
]]></fr:tex> extends to a function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b^\sharp  \colon  \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x\colon \mathsf {toProp}\,A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x\colon \mathsf {toProp}\,A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x\colon \mathsf {toProp}\,A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x\colon \mathsf {toProp}\,A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}} Bx]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
            <html:p>When we have an element of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {toProp}\,A]]></fr:tex>, we will say that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is <html:em><html:strong>inhabited</html:strong></html:em>.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
