            <fr:title text="biinverse">biinverse</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:meta name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000U.agda" type="external">erct-000U.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>A <html:em><html:strong>biinverse</html:strong></html:em> to a function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A \to  B]]></fr:tex> is defined to be a pair of a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000Y.xml" title="section-retraction pair" addr="forest://erct/erct-000Y" type="local">section</fr:link> and a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000Y.xml" title="section-retraction pair" addr="forest://erct/erct-000Y" type="local">retraction</fr:link> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex>. We will refer to a function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\to  B]]></fr:tex> equipped with a biinverse as a <html:em><html:strong>biinvertible function</html:strong></html:em>.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
